snippet.textDisplay: When I was younger, and I'd get scam calls, I'd answer and breath loudly into the phone for like 2 minutes. Sometimes they would say something like "sir?....sir?....." Or "mam?...." And when there was no answer, they'd either hang up, or I'd progressively get quieter and hang up myself. I'd die laughing afterwards because I thought that it was hilarious that I was scaring the crap out of some telemarketer or scammer... I don't get them nearly as much now, though.
